# define.passage-statuses

only `'passed'` constitutes valid passage.

| status | is passage? |
|--------|-------------|
| `'passed'` | **yes** — driver explicitly marked complete |
| `'approved'` | no — permission granted, not action taken |
| `'blocked'` | no — cannot proceed |
| `'rewound'` | no — prior passage revoked |

guard flow: `review → judge → approve → judge → pass`

approval = permission. passage = action.

> passage requires intent. only explicit `--as passed` constitutes passage.
